Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.48,0:00:04.23,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Who's that?! Someone's coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.40,0:00:14.66,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,I don't know who he is, but he's not normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.66,0:00:15.66,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Polnareff!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.66,0:00:17.41,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Either way, I'll kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.62,0:00:22.58,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,A playing card? {SEE?! I WASNT JOKING WHEN I SAID JAPANESE PEOPLE CALL NORMAL PLAYING CARDS TRUMPS!}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.58,0:00:26.63,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Welcome, Master Joestar. \NWe have been awaiting your arrival.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.13,0:00:30.67,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I am the butler of this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.67,0:00:32.97,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,You may call me D'Arby.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.01,0:00:34.97,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,D'Arby?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.97,0:00:38.01,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Yes. Terence T. D'Arby.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.01,0:00:42.43,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,The man who you previously \Ndefeated beyond recovery, Daniel J. D'Arby...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.41,0:00:44.48,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,...is my older brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.06,0:00:48.69,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,You're D'Arby the Gambler's younger brother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.11,0:00:52.36,Main,Abdul,0,0,0,,Are you here to avenge your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.99,0:01:00.79,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Not at all. I wouldn't dream of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.16,0:01:08.63,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Didn't he tell you this already? \NThe fault lies with the loser for being deceived in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.63,0:01:11.09,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I also believe this to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.09,0:01:13.38,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,My brother is at fault for failing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.76,0:01:16.55,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I bear no ill will towards you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.18,0:01:21.26,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,My brother is my brother, and I am myself. \NDo not think any differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.72,0:01:24.39,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,He is ten years my senior.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.39,0:01:29.86,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I respect my brother to an extent, \Nbut we come from different generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.86,0:01:33.19,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,He's the type of man who has to \Nrely on deception and cheating to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.19,0:01:37.70,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,He was only capable of defeating those\N who were either old-fashioned or complete amateurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.70,0:01:44.50,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,It would seem Lord Dio also recognized this, \Nwhich is why he chose me to be his butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.37,0:01:48.12,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.54,0:01:55.88,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,If you are so eager to fight me, please, step into the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.17,0:01:58.97,Main,Abdul,0,0,0,,Everyone, do not carelessly rush inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.97,0:02:02.64,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,There's no time for this. Hurry and take us to Dio.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.64,0:02:05.64,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Jotaro! Be careful! He's trying something!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.60,0:02:12.23,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Terence T. D'Arby. \NHis Stand, Divine Atum, suggests the God, Atum! {I'll take redundant CR edits for $600}{Atum-shin}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.78,0:02:17.70,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,H-Hey, he brought out his Stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.70,0:02:19.74,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Don't see that too often.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.74,0:02:22.70,Main,Abdul,0,0,0,,It has been quite some time since we\N faced someone who openly used their Stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.70,0:02:24.20,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,So who will it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.20,0:02:25.91,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Who shall my first opponent be?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.91,0:02:30.21,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,What a pain in the ass! Jotaro, give him a good beating!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.42,0:02:35.51,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Let's make a bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.51,0:02:38.63,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,The first attack Star Platinum will attempt to use against me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.63,0:02:40.39,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,...is a left-handed blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.93,0:02:46.52,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,He will try to attack me with a punch using his left arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.52,0:02:47.10,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Let's make a bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.10,0:02:50.81,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter!\N It's all the same if you hit him with everything you got!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.81,0:02:52.56,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.90,0:02:55.32,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Hurry up and hit him, Jotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:56.53,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Ora! {Gawd it's been a while since we've gotten one of these :D}{OraGasm}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.53,0:03:01.53,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,What? H-He dodged?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.86,0:03:03.62,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,He's so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.62,0:03:04.95,Main,Abdul,0,0,0,,Inconceivable!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.62,0:03:13.67,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Such a shame. I suppose I've lost this bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:18.38,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I enjoy gambling like my brother,\N but I am not very good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.26,0:03:23.01,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,To reward you for besting me,\N allow me to take you to a fantastical world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.68,0:03:26.18,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,What? A hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.18,0:03:28.56,Main,Abdul,0,0,0,,Curses! It really was a trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:30.02,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Jotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.02,0:03:33.86,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Jotaro's being pulled into the hole!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.19,0:03:35.48,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Get him out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.40,0:03:41.61,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Very well. You gentlemen may enter, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.61,0:03:42.70,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Wha{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.70,0:03:45.45,Main,Polnareff,0,0,0,,Mr. Joestar! Kakyoin!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.45,0:03:47.74,Main,Abdul,0,0,0,,Wait! It is too dangerous to follow them!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.74,0:03:50.37,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Abdul, can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.87,0:03:56.00,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,If you don't hear from us in ten minutes, set the mansion on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.54,0:03:59.26,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Got it, Abdul?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.26,0:04:01.67,Main,Jojobros,0,0,0,,Mr. Joestar!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.14,0:04:11.23,Title 3,title,0,0,0,,{\fad(753,855)\pos(146,877)}Episode 40: D'Arby the Gamer Part 1
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.40,0:04:21.07,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,This illusion... Are we above ground, or below?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.57,0:04:29.08,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,The feeling of water at my feet... This reality...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.08,0:04:30.75,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,It's too convincing...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.75,0:04:33.41,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,What the hell is he up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.59,0:04:46.43,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Gramps, Kakyoin... Explain this mystery to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.14,0:04:48.60,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,His Stand...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.60,0:04:51.60,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,It definitely knew I would throw a right punch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.02,0:04:53.23,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.98,0:04:59.11,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,If we can't solve this mystery, he'll beat us for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.23,0:05:02.07,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Would you care for a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.49,0:05:06.86,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,The drinks are real, of course, \Nand I assure you they are not poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.86,0:05:09.41,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Are we inside the mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.83,0:05:10.83,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.70,0:05:13.25,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Where inside the mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.62,0:05:14.91,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I cannot say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.91,0:05:16.17,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Are we below ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.17,0:05:17.88,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.17,0:05:23.34,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Was this illusion created by a Stand?{This was originally "Is this illusion your Stand?", which is straight up incorrect because it is in fact NOT caused by D'Arby's Stand, but rather some other Stand, lol. CR mega-fail}{It's especially bad when you consider his next question is if the Stand belongs to him, to which the answer is no, lol}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.71,0:05:24.84,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.13,0:05:27.22,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Is it your Stand's power?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.64,0:05:28.55,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,It is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.93,0:05:29.89,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Is it Dio's?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.26,0:05:31.06,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,It is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:32.47,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Whose is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:34.35,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,You needn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.81,0:05:40.31,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,According to the Speedwagon Foundation's intel, \Nthere are at least two or three other Stand users here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.31,0:05:41.40,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.40,0:05:43.86,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,You needn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.53,0:05:48.03,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,I guess we're not getting any straight answers out of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.36,0:05:50.87,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I could lie to you if I wished.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.87,0:05:55.83,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,But unlike my brother, I refuse to lie or play tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.87,0:05:59.79,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,So what's your point?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.79,0:06:04.38,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,If we aren't able to defeat you, we can't proceed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.09,0:06:06.76,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.76,0:06:09.05,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,That's the right idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.05,0:06:13.22,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,His needlessly polite attitude... \NIt's starting to get on my nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.97,0:06:16.81,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Did you forget this is one against three?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.81,0:06:20.31,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,We're in a hurry, and the three of us are prepared to fight you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.81,0:06:24.11,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Please, no need to rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.11,0:06:26.83,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Before you do that, I have something to show you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.17,0:06:29.99,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,My collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.99,0:06:31.49,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Collection?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.79,0:06:45.84,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,While not quite to the same extent as my brother, \NI also enjoy collecting things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.84,0:06:52.14,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Indeed, one likes to hear compliments about \Ntheir precious collection when showing it to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:54.22,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,They can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.22,0:06:58.18,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Dolls? A-Are those really dolls?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:06:59.69,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,No, Kakyoin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.69,0:07:04.40,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,We're dealing with one of the D'Arby brothers.\N They can't just be normal dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.78,0:07:12.53,Main,Creepy fuck,0,0,0,,D-D'Arby...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.66,0:07:16.54,Main,Creepy fuck,0,0,0,,Will you please speak to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.54,0:07:18.95,Main,Creepy fuck,0,0,0,,I'm begging you, speak to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.95,0:07:21.71,Main,Creepy fuck,0,0,0,,Speak to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.80,0:07:28.05,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Oh my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.05,0:07:31.22,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,They're alive... These dolls are alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.22,0:07:33.30,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,You freak! They're souls!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.64,0:07:36.56,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,My hobby is doll making.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.56,0:07:40.94,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,However, I like to have real souls inhabit them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.94,0:07:44.61,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Perhaps showing you this was ill-advised, \Nbut such is the power of my Stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.36,0:07:51.11,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,My brother found pleasure in lining up his little soul coins in a row, \Nbut I found that rather simple and mundane.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.11,0:07:55.03,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I change their clothes and even speak to them on occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.03,0:07:56.12,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,For example...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.83,0:07:59.16,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,This young woman's name is Sonia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.12,0:08:01.79,Secondary,Creepy fuck,0,0,0,,D'Arby! Oh, D'Arby!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.16,0:08:02.62,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I love when she tells me her beautiful love stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.79,0:08:03.58,Secondary,Creepy fuck,0,0,0,,D'Arby...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.62,0:08:04.54,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Isn't her skin beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.54,0:08:07.17,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,It makes me proud to show off a beauty like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.54,0:08:06.42,Secondary,Creepy fuck,0,0,0,,D'Arby...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.71,0:08:11.97,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Dr. Elliott is a serial killer. He killed eight people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.97,0:08:14.84,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I love when he tells me about the people he murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.84,0:08:18.18,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I constructed his glasses and stethoscope myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.43,0:08:22.39,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right! \NThere's still something I haven't shown you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.39,0:08:26.40,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,A young lad from Japan; the video game master, Tatsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.40,0:08:30.23,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,His IQ of 190 makes him quite formidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.23,0:08:34.11,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Beating him and taking his soul was no simple task.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.82,0:08:34.11,Secondary,Creepy fuck,0,0,0,,Mama... Mama! Mama!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.53,0:08:36.82,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,You and your brother are lunatics.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.82,0:08:40.04,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Actually, you're probably even worse than him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.04,0:08:41.87,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,You're getting on my nerves!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.87,0:08:45.00,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,You act like a gentleman, but you're nothing but scum.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.00,0:08:46.13,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,You make me sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.00,0:08:51.59,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,By the way, I'm sure you're aware of this from your run-in with my brother, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.59,0:08:54.88,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,...aren't human souls truly a mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.88,0:09:01.64,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Once a person has admitted defeat, \Nthe energy in their soul instantly drops to almost nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.02,0:09:05.69,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I prepare for that moment and take their soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.69,0:09:09.02,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,This is how my brother's Stand and mine work!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.02,0:09:12.15,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,We've heard enough! You're {\i1}really {\i0}getting on my nerves!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.15,0:09:15.82,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,We'll make quick work of you, then move on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.82,0:09:18.16,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,You haven't heard quite enough yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.16,0:09:23.00,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,You should know, Jotaro, \Nthat you have no choice but to play at my pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.41,0:09:30.54,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Jotaro, it gave you quite a shock when \NI correctly predicted which arm you would use, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.54,0:09:33.88,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,How exactly I did it must still be a mystery to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.30,0:09:39.18,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,At that moment, I just barely grazed your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.18,0:09:42.14,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,What do you think happened when I did that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.23,0:09:49.06,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.06,0:09:50.48,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,What the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.90,0:09:55.36,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I left my Atum's hand attached to your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.36,0:10:00.24,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,If I were to crush your arm, \NI'm sure it would greatly please Lord Dio.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.57,0:10:09.04,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,However, if I did that, Kakyoin and Joestar \Nwould instantly attack me, and I would be deftly defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.04,0:10:10.88,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I would rather avoid that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.50,0:10:15.01,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,So how about this, gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.01,0:10:17.30,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Why don't we play a little game and gamble our souls?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.30,0:10:18.59,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.59,0:10:23.43,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,If I admit absolute defeat, I will let go of his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:28.69,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Gimme a break. No choice but to stay at your pace, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.06,0:10:34.86,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,True as it is, you're gonna regret ever tricking me, D'Arby.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.86,0:10:41.82,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I would be absolutely tickled if you said, "I will play a game and bet my soul."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.82,0:10:45.49,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,However, the first to play will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.83,0:10:49.08,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,...Kakyoin. You're up first.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:51.71,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Hey, what gives?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.71,0:10:55.25,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,I should be the first to beat your ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.25,0:11:00.01,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,You and Joestar are related by blood, \Nand as such, share no such relation to Kakyoin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.01,0:11:08.43,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,If I succeeded in taking your souls, and Kakyoin decided not to \Nattempt to win them back, he may choose to attack me with his Stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.52,0:11:11.52,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,You're really full of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.52,0:11:14.86,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,You talk like you won already.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.86,0:11:18.65,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Very well. I'll be your first opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.65,0:11:19.36,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:20.86,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Kakyoin!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.86,0:11:23.20,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,It's fine. I feel confident.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.62,0:11:27.83,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I happen to have some experience playing video games.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.25,0:11:32.46,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I challenge you to a game of F{\fs50\alpha(FF)}★{\alpha\fs}Mega.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.25,0:11:32.46,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,{\fs50\pos(1262.5,1043)}★{Fadeout, comment this line back in once you've fixed the placement.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:38.13,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I bet my soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.76,0:11:47.97,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I bet my soul! {same as above}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.52,0:11:49.85,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.85,0:11:52.14,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Kakyoin!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.14,0:11:54.98,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,You don't need to go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.98,0:11:56.52,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.52,0:12:01.65,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Since you have that thing attached to your arm, \Nthere's a chance you could make a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.65,0:12:08.20,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,D'Arby, do we have your word that if you lose, your Stand will let go of Jotaro's arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.69,0:12:36.06,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,There's nothing wrong with the TV, console, or game cartridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.06,0:12:38.86,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,You could find this video game anywhere in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.32,0:12:42.61,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Do not confuse me for my brother. I shall not cheat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.53,0:12:46.41,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Now, let us begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.95,0:12:47.87,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.33,0:12:58.09,Narrator,Game,0,0,0,,F{\fs50\alpha(FF)}★{\alpha\fs}Mega! {Using the narrator font for the game announcer} {What universe do they live in where a game with 3D graphics at this level of detail can fit on a cartridge? xD}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.33,0:12:58.09,Narrator,Game,0,0,0,,{\fs47\pos(902,1043)}★
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.51,0:13:03.17,Narrator,Game,0,0,0,,Select your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.17,0:13:06.05,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Start by selecting your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.05,0:13:06.84,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.26,0:13:13.14,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,So you decided on car #28, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.14,0:13:16.94,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Mine is #15, since I was born on January 5th.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.94,0:13:21.11,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.11,0:13:24.11,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Enough pleasantries, just go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.41,0:13:30.08,Narrator,Game,0,0,0,,Race start in...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.08,0:13:31.20,Narrator,Game,0,0,0,,Five...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.46,0:13:41.46,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,That technique he's using to quickly mash the acceleration button...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.46,0:13:43.59,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,It's so he can get a boost start! {He says start dash, but the English version of this phrase is boost start.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.59,0:13:44.38,Narrator,Game,0,0,0,,Three...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.72,0:13:49.01,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Damn! I won't be able to get a boost like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.92,0:13:46.88,Secondary,Game,0,0,0,,{\i1}Two...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.01,0:13:51.31,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,He's going to get ahead of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.31,0:13:52.26,Narrator,Game,0,0,0,,One...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.77,0:13:55.23,Narrator,Game,0,0,0,,Start!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.04,0:14:17.29,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,He's blocking me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.58,0:14:21.50,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,My victory is assured if I can keep this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.50,0:14:24.30,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,He'll never be able to get past me at this point!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.30,0:14:29.51,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,And unfortunately for you, \NI, D'Arby, never make a mistake during a race!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.51,0:14:31.68,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,How terribly naïve of you, Kakyoin!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.60,0:14:39.44,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.78,0:14:49.07,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Kakyoin, just how much have you played this game before?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.07,0:14:51.07,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,You needn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.07,0:14:51.87,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.87,0:14:54.16,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,This is your chance, Kakyoin!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.16,0:14:57.70,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Get your car back on course, and keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.21,0:15:00.96,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,That technique just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.96,0:15:04.00,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Pulling off something like that \Ngoes beyond being experienced at F{\fs50\alpha(FF)}★{\alpha\fs}Mega...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.96,0:15:04.00,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,{\fs50\pos(1308.5,1043)}★{\alpha\fs}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.34,0:15:09.84,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,He has a bold personality despite his outward anxious appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.77,0:15:21.15,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,It's a tie! They're right next to each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.15,0:15:24.57,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,No. Kakyoin ended up on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.11,0:15:29.32,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,If they hit a corner together, \Nwhoever's on the outside is shit out of luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.32,0:15:34.91,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,355 kilometers per hour... 358... 360...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.91,0:15:36.91,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,We'll hit the first corner in three seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.91,0:15:39.12,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I can take the corner at this speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.54,0:15:41.42,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I'll go through it at full throttle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.83,0:15:43.79,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Two... One!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.72,0:15:54.09,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,They made it together!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.09,0:15:56.31,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,They turned together at the same time and speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.31,0:15:57.35,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,They're neck and neck!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.72,0:15:59.77,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I've taken a liking to you, Kakyoin!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.77,0:16:02.90,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,You aren't phased in the slightest despite gambling your soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.90,0:16:05.36,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,You've risen above fear for the sake of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.36,0:16:11.24,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,As someone who is capable of competing with me at this level, \NI deem you worthy to be a part of my doll collection!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.70,0:16:14.91,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Kakyoin Noriaki thought to himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.91,0:16:17.66,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Me? Rise above fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.20,0:16:22.71,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Thanks. I've had training.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.71,0:16:26.34,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Six months ago, when I met your master, Dio...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.34,0:16:31.59,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,...he planted a flesh bud in my brain,\N showing me the true meaning of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.13,0:16:33.34,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,In that moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.34,0:16:39.06,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,The moment I met Dio...\N I realized what a terrifying monster he truly was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.06,0:16:44.23,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I lost feeling in my legs, \Nevery hair on my body stood on end, and I froze in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.23,0:16:52.69,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,As I stared at Dio in a frozen panic, \Nthe paralysis made my hair stand on end even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.69,0:16:55.78,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,My stomach convulsed, and I became nauseous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.78,0:16:58.03,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I nearly threw up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.03,0:17:00.54,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Then Dio spoke these words as he gazed at me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.54,0:17:03.71,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,His voice was gentle, as if speaking to a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.71,0:17:05.46,Flashback,Dio,0,0,0,,"Kakyoin...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.63,0:17:08.63,Flashback,Dio,0,0,0,,...you have nothing to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.50,0:17:11.13,Flashback,Dio,0,0,0,,Let us be friends."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.51,0:17:15.18,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I despise what I thought next! After I heard that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.55,0:17:20.51,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,...I was relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.51,0:17:23.68,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,To be honest, I felt relief from the bottom of my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.48,0:17:27.69,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,It gave me relief to know I would keep on living!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.44,0:17:32.15,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,But... it was humiliating. I can't forgive him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.15,0:17:34.32,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I've never felt so humiliated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.32,0:17:36.11,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I couldn't forgive myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.11,0:17:38.82,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I despised myself for giving in to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.24,0:17:43.20,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Jotaro saved me, and that's why I went on this journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.20,0:17:46.08,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I will never return to being that pathetic Kakyoin ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:51.17,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,D'Arby, that's why I decided to gamble my soul in this challenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.92,0:17:56.72,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Three... two... one!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.76,0:17:59.09,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,They went together again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.55,0:18:01.35,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,The third corner!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.35,0:18:07.94,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,That's why I, Kakyoin Noriaki, refuse to allow my nerves to make me mess up even once!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.52,0:18:10.31,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I'll show you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.31,0:18:13.94,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,All right! The fifth corner! Together again!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.94,0:18:15.86,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,They keep going through them at the same time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.86,0:18:18.86,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,K-Kakyoin... you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.86,0:18:21.20,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Next is the sixth corner!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.95,0:18:25.83,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,A boost tunnel is visible once you pass the sixth corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.83,0:18:31.00,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Going through the tunnel allows you to reach speeds of up to 850 kilometers per hour!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.00,0:18:33.50,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I must enter the tunnel no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.50,0:18:37.26,Thoughts,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,But the tunnel is only big enough to accommodate one car!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.72,0:18:42.30,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,If they keep racing neck and neck, \None of them won't be able to enter the tunnel!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.72,0:18:44.56,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,The sixth corner!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.56,0:18:46.14,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Again, they're going together!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.77,0:18:51.02,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,It's the tunnel! I see the tunnel!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.90,0:18:55.36,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Kakyoin, don't let him push you out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.11,0:18:58.99,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,It seems you haven't realized yet, Kakyoin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.99,0:19:01.37,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Do you think you can just push me out?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.37,0:19:05.45,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Take a look at your #28's remaining power.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.58,0:19:10.29,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,K-Kakyoin has less!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.29,0:19:14.96,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,At the race's start, you spun and were blown away by my blocking maneuver.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.30,0:19:20.13,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Didn't you realize you would have less energy after that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.43,0:19:28.81,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Two seconds until the tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.27,0:19:30.69,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,You're gonna crash!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.69,0:19:32.15,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Let him have the lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.15,0:19:34.52,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Go into the tunnel after D'Arby!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.52,0:19:35.82,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.82,0:19:39.61,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,If I let him enter the tunnel first, I'll have no chance of winning!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.61,0:19:41.49,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,One second until the tunnel!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.49,0:19:42.91,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Kakyoin!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.24,0:19:48.70,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Whoa! He tilted his car!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.67,0:19:54.67,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I never thought you would enter on the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.67,0:19:59.63,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Y-You did it, Kakyoin! \NYour mental game is stronger than his!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.63,0:20:00.97,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.97,0:20:02.47,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Silence! You're a distraction!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.93,0:20:09.68,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,He's ramming him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.06,0:20:12.69,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,It matters not how little power I have remaining!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.69,0:20:16.27,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I'll take this next turn even if it's only\N one hundredth of a second faster than Kakyoin!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.27,0:20:18.78,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I'll take the shortest path even if \Nit's only by one thousandth of a milimeter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.78,0:20:21.40,Thoughts,D'Arby,0,0,0,,And I'll get through this tunnel even if it's but a moment faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.03,0:20:24.78,Narrator,Game,0,0,0,,No radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.28,0:20:28.45,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,H-Hey, what's wrong? I can't see them anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.45,0:20:31.91,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,We have to make it through the tunnel in total darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.91,0:20:32.54,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.54,0:20:35.88,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,An absolute darkness where radar is completely useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.88,0:20:41.97,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,There are eight curves, a mine, and a cannon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.97,0:20:44.30,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,The tunnel's exit lies at the end of the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.89,0:20:46.97,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,One mistake and you'll hit the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.97,0:20:50.97,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,But I've memorized the timing needed to take each corner!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.97,0:20:52.35,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,And so has D'Arby...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.06,0:20:58.90,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,That sound means he's taking a corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.87,0:21:16.79,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,What's going on? Where the hell are they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.79,0:21:18.79,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Who's going faster?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.79,0:21:19.59,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,Three...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.25,0:21:21.55,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Two...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.80,0:21:22.76,Main,Both,0,0,0,,One!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.76,0:21:24.55,Main,Both,0,0,0,,Cannon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.97,0:21:32.22,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,For a second, I saw them in the light of the cannon blast!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.22,0:21:35.48,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,Kakyoin is only a bit behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.31,0:21:41.23,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,I can see the exit! They're exiting the tunnel!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.78,0:21:47.91,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,D'Arby is definitely going faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.91,0:21:50.66,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,He's ahead by a car length!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.66,0:21:52.33,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,Victory is mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.42,0:23:28.42,Next Episode,,0,0,0,,{\fs120\pos(960,730)}Next Episode{PREVIEW IS NOT UP TO DATE}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.13,0:23:29.30,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,I never let my guard down regardless of the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.30,0:23:31.59,Main,Kakyoin,0,0,0,,You have less power remaining!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.59,0:23:33.18,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,In my hands, I now hold his soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.18,0:23:34.64,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,Quit screwing around, Jotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.64,0:23:36.18,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,I know the rules of baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.18,0:23:38.10,Main,D'Arby,0,0,0,,You can't back out now!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.10,0:23:39.98,Main,Jotaro,0,0,0,,I expected more encouraging words under these circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.98,0:23:41.44,Main,Joseph,0,0,0,,It's pathetic!
